description: Basic Python coding standards and style guidelines

## PEP 8 Compliance
- Follow official Python style guide
- Use tools like black, flake8 for formatting
- Limit lines to 79 characters

## Naming Conventions
- Use snake_case for functions and variables
- Use PascalCase for class names
- Use meaningful, descriptive names

## Code Organization
- Write modular, reusable functions and classes
- Avoid code duplication
- Use constants instead of hardcoded values

## Pythonic Practices
- Utilize Python's built-in features
- Prefer list comprehensions for simple loops
- Follow Python idioms and conventions

